reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Form Fitting but Really Comfortable
reviews.reviewText: The cut and especially the V crossover waist detail of these leggings/pants is very flattering.I'm 5'2" and 115 lbs and ordered size small. They fit well though I did have to cut the bottom hems roughly an inch and a half to get the right length. So nice not to have to worry about hemming these - you just (carefully) cut them with a pair of scissors.After a tough couple days of working out and feeling tired and sore these boot-cut legging are my go-to. Though these are form fitting they are really comfortable and don't make you feel like you've been stuffed into a sausage casing like some workout legging do. Sounds strange, but they're relaxing to put on.Well-made, straight and neat stitching. Pockets sit on hips at a comfortable spot. Easy care - throw them in washer gentle cycle and dryer at low heat and that's it.If you're a pet owner and you order the black keep a lint remover handy. Made the mistake of sitting on the couch and letting my little monster Chi sit on my lap before heading to the gym and realized once I got there that I was covered in Chi "glitter." These are such a deep black everything shows up on them so be forewarned.Decently priced for a well-made, comfortable and most flattering pair of boot-cut leggings.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Yoga pants with pockets
reviews.reviewText: I really am loving these yoga pants. First the fit: the crossover belly band is flattering and forgiving for those of us "fluffier" individuals, I love the flare at the bottom, giving a much more flattering fit that the "skinny" type ankles that give me the silhouette of an ice cream cone 😉.The material is stretchy, but offers good support to keep some of the lumps and bulges on the down low. The best part of these pants is that they have full-sized pockets, I think that manufacturers are starting to understand that women have been deprived of real pockets for so long that when we get actual functioning pockets, it's a halleluiah moment.I've also washed and dried these several times without any pilling or fading, and the $28.99 is a great price for the quality of the pant.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Fit true to size and comfortable but rolls down if you don't have a flat stomach
reviews.reviewText: These yoga pants are breathable, comfortable, not sheer, and a great length for me (I'm 5'2). They fit true to size and the style and color are as expected. My only complaint is that the waist of these pants roll down if you don't have a flat stomach. I'm not big in that area but; I do have normal curves and mother organs. Any time I sat or even moved a certain way while doing chores; these rolled down and exposed my belly. I just wear long, oversized shirts with them now. I removed a star for the rolling. Every other aspect was nice quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice Leggings but long
reviews.reviewText: These leggings seem to be pretty good quality. They have a nice feel to them and a lot of stretch. When I first opened them I didn’t think they were going to even get over my thighs, but they stretched and fit over my hips & waist. You can see from the last picture the waist looks pretty small for a large. I would have preferred an XL, but they only had the large available so figured I would try them since I do anticipate losing weight. If I do I expect them to fit better. They are a bit long on me, which doesn’t bother me as I like my pants long. These are fine for me since I won’t really be wearing them out, just to lounge in the house and work out. But with a nice top & shoes they could definitely be worn out & about depending on where you would be going. They are not at all see through which is a big plus and they have pockets. For reference I am 5’2” about 175lbs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fit and Look Great
reviews.reviewText: These are nice yoga pants. I ordered my normal size and they fit true to size. The material is so nice and soft with plenty of stretch. They cross waist is really flattering and lots of great control so they look super on. I'm tall and the length is perfect, I really hate when they're short and that’s not an issue with these and the flare at the bottom is perfect.They seem to be made well, the seams are all straight and there are not loose threads. The material is a decent weight and I don't fine them see through at all. They really hug you nicely but have lots of give so you can easily move and stretch. I think my favorite feature are the pockets. You usually can't get those in yoga pants. I was initially concerned they would look bulky and look funny but you can't even see them. These will be getting lots of wear.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These are super comfortable. I am also a pretty average height and they do not drag the floor. I feel like they sit just right with tennis shoes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Flare Pants making a come back!
reviews.reviewText: I love these flare leggings! I am 5’1” and weigh 177 pounds and got these in a size medium and they are snug enough to hold in my spare tire. They are also long for my short legs. The fabric is very soft and very stretchy. It is also durable fabric and not see through when you’re bending over. I am very happy with these and will definitely be buying more.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2024
reviews.reviewText: They're okay, a little shorter than I'd like and I have short legs at 5'5". Wanted to wear these out in public but I look ridiculous. Seriously looks like I'm ready for a flood.
